                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-218-off1218 t18301209-218-victim1860"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-218-person1861">
                  JAMES 
                  BARKWAY
               <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1861" type="surname" value="BARKWAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1861" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1861" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This property was taken out of a shed adjoining my house in <placeName id="t18301209-218-crimeloc1220">Wellington-place, Stepney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-218-crimeloc1220" type="placeName" value="Wellington-place, Stepney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-218-crimeloc1220" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-218-off1218 t18301209-218-crimeloc1220"></join>; it belonged to Mr. Moore - it was distrained for rent, and put into my custody; I went out on the 5th of November, in consequence of information, and saw the prisoner about one hundred yards from my shed, carrying a bundle; there was an accomplice with him, but he got away - the prisoner dropped the bed, and I fell over it - I called Stop thief! the prisoner threw down the bundle.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did he not tell<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183012090104"></xptr>you the other man gave them to him to carry? A. He said so at the Police-office - a child told my wife of this, but she is not here.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-218-person1862">
                  JOHN 
                  HULL
               <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1862" type="surname" value="HULL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1862" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1862" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner - I saw him coming up the road with something which he dropped, and the witness fell over it; I took the prisoner without a hat - he said before the Magistrate that the other man gave him the bundle to carry.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM MOORE. This property was left there for the person it belonged to to fetch it away; I am answerable for it - I have been called William Thomas, but my name is only William.</p>
               <p>Q. How do you write your name? A. William Moore, and I was christened William Moore.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Do you believe you were not christened 
               <persName id="t18301209-218-person1863">
                  William 
                  Thomas
               <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1863" type="surname" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1863" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-218-person1863" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ? A. No; I have some property disputed in Chancery, and it is in the name of William Moore - I have been called Thomas, and my aunt said my name was not Thomas.</p>
               <p>Four witnesses gave the prisoner a good character; one of whom stated he would take him into his employ.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 18.</p>
               <p>
